{"key":"processedPost-9344897","value":{"id":9344897,"first":9323247,"last":9344897,"when":1228170212,"utime":"12/02/08 12:23 AM","cleanedPost":"I'd find a blower that can deliver 500 to 600 cfm at 1\" static pressure for a 2 X 2 blower.&nbsp; You want about 400 to 450 cfm leaving the face of the filter, but since blowers are not 100% efficient, and the fact that you'll have friction, etc., you want to add 20% or so.<br />You should be able to go to a local furnace repair shop and they probably have a few junked out old units in the back that they'll sell a blower cheaply from.&nbsp; Let them know what cfm you're looking for and they can try to match it.&nbsp; If the motor is slightly too large, you can always block off part of the intake to cut down on flow, or purchase a <a href=\"http://www.littlegreenhouse.com/accessory/controls2.shtml\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">motor speed controller</a>.<br />RR"}}